.TH man 8 "00 May 2018" "1.0" "Todolist man page"
.SH NAME
TODO LIST
.SH SYNOPSIS
[ --version] : You can check this version.
.br
[ --help], [-h] : You can see the directions.
.br
[--today], [-t] : You can see your schedule that you need to do today.
.br
[--all], [-a] : You can see all of your schedule.
.br
[--week], [-w] : You can see your schedule that you need to finish in this week.
.br
[--month], [-m] : You can see your schedule that you need to finish in this month.
.br
[--add] : Add your schedule.
.br
[--list] : Check your schedule by several options.
.br
[--remove] : Remove schedule.
.br
[--modify] : Modify your schedule of state, tag, due date.
.br
[--setOrder] : Set order options. 
.br
[--setTag] : Set tags.
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Add todo 
: You can add your schedule by due date and time.
.br 
.B List todo
: You can view your schedule by some option (All / Expired / Not Expired / Finished / Unfinished / Tag)
.br 
.B Modify todo 
: Enter a number that point the schedule you want to modify
.br 
.B Remove todo
 : You can remove your own schedule by schedule number. 
.br 
.B Order option
 : You can set order options about list. 
.br 
.B Tag setting
 : You can set or modify your own tags. (Show all tags / Remove in current list / Remove all)
.SH OPTIONS
The TODO List 
.SH BUG REPORT
Please make issues on our GitHub.
.br
https://github.com/dudu0166/OSS_SW_7_TodoList
.SH AUTHOR
Team 7